        "id": "xoOViAxi-tvacPdf",
        "title": "Text 1",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Gary and Julia were trying to figure out how much water is used per person each day. They found information from a recent study. </p><ul><li>Approximately 4.10 • 10<sup>11</sup> gallons of water is used each day in the United States. </li><li>There are approximately 330,000,000 people in the United States.</li></ul><p>To find the answer, they use the expression (4.10 x 10<sup>11</sup>) ÷ (330,000,000). They have different methods for carrying out the calculations. </p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "3oy5TEoMOgYM9d9o",
        "title": "Text 3",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p><strong>Gary&#x27;s Method</strong></p><p>I wrote both numbers as millions. </p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "WTyLieqD6cvvQsht",
        "title": "Gary's Method 1",
        "content": {
          "type": "Expression",
          "latexStr": "4.10\\times10^{11}=410,000\\times10^6"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "GpXcn-VSydrf3nqU",
        "title": "Gary's Method 2",
        "content": {
          "type": "Expression",
          "latexStr": "330,000,000=330\\times10^6"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "RAH6CAB2KJsW1GDg",
        "title": "Dividing gives",
        "content": {
          "type": "Expression",
          "latexStr": "410,000\\div330\\approx1,242"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "5j_X9HLjHfq7lr9i",
        "title": "Text 4",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>My result is 1,242 gallons per day.</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "K6f1bW_MKUdGz0iX",
        "title": "Text 5",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p><strong>Julia&#x27;s Method</strong></p><p>I changes 330,000,000 to 3.30 x 10<sup>8</sup>. Then I rewrote the problem as</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "zsF-MIa9jC5Y_Z4n",
        "title": "Julia's Equation",
        "content": {
          "type": "Expression",
          "latexStr": "\\frac{4.10\\times10^{11}}{3.30\\times10^8}=\\frac{4.10}{3.30}\\times\\frac{10^{11}}{10^8}=1.24\\times10^3"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "mSbP_G58zURll4U-",
        "title": "Text 6",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>I know that 10<sup>11</sup> ÷ 10<sup>8</sup> = 10<sup>3</sup> because 10<sup>8</sup> ·10<sup>3 </sup>= 10<sup>11</sup> . So the answer is about 1.24 x 10<sup>3</sup>  gallons per day for each person.</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "mBTN4KxwQhtfZs1b",
        "title": "Text 2",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Which of these methods makes sense to you? What other method could you use?</p><p>What percent of the water used in the United States each day went to each of the following? </p><p>                                  Irrigation (1.28 • 10<sup>11</sup> gallons of water per day) </p><p>                                   Livestock (2.14 • 10<sup>9</sup>gallons of water per day) </p>"
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
